###################################################################
#################### construct-world-object #######################

Propose an operator with the following structure:

(<s> ^operator <o> +)
(<o> ^name construct-world-object
     ^source-type << smem-obj epmem-obj imagined-obj perception-obj >>
     ^source-obj <obj>
     ^destination <dest>
     ^result-name <obj-name>
     ^smem-obj <lti>) ### OPTIONAL: If this is an object with smem info, put the link here

Will create a world object from the given source-obj and copy it as:
(<dest> ^<obj-name> <world-obj>)

Supports creating objects from the following sources:

^source-type smem-obj
   source-obj is an LTI for a representation of an object in semantic memory

^source-type epmem-obj
   source-obj is the root identifier for a world object retrieved from episodic memory

^source-type imagined-obj
   source-obj is the root identifier for an object that is not from perception, 
      but has a similar structure

^source-type perception-obj
   source-obj is the root identifier of an object from the input-link
   



